      "fill": "semi",
      "w": 460,
      "label": "ONE tool: consensus_respond(action, payload). One tool -> the model can't call the WRONG tool. The brain restates the phase-legal action set each turn (memory holds the rest of the protocol)."
    },
    {
      "id": "n-brain",
      "color": "light-green",
      "fill": "semi",
      "w": 460,
      "label": "Graded stateful brain (works on ANY transport): valid -> ack + advance state \u00b7 invalid -> correct + retry \u00b7 repeated -> EJECT. Closed-loop + bounded = compliance, not just tolerance."
    },
    {
      "id": "n-opt",
      "color": "orange",
      "fill": "semi",
      "w": 460,
      "label": "Hard enforcement (API tool_choice / strict / enum) = OPTIMIZATION: first answer always legal, skip retries. NOT a gate. MCP: enum is a hint; the loop covers the miss. RISK: eject must not dual-kill the peer."
    }
